Use the EthereumJS `InterpreterStep`, `Message`, and `EvmRunCallOpts` types where appropriate. If the existing tracer types in `packages/actions/src/common/` define the right shapes, reference those instead.

## TS2379 (ExactOptionalPropertyTypes for ImpersonatedTxData) — 8 errors

Files:
- packages/actions/src/debug/debugIntermediateRootsProcedure.js:99
- packages/actions/src/debug/debugTraceBlockProcedure.js:113
- packages/actions/src/debug/debugTraceChainProcedure.js:154
- packages/actions/src/debug/debugTraceTransactionProcedure.js:130

The H09 fix likely builds an object literal with `to?: Address` (present but possibly undefined) and passes it to a function whose parameter type is `ImpersonatedTxData` which doesn't allow undefined for `to`. Fix by either:
(a) Conditionally spreading: `...(to !== undefined ? { to } : {})`
(b) Adding `| undefined` to the `to` field on ImpersonatedTxData if that's the right semantic.
Pick (a) when the source is a transaction-shaped union, (b) when the receiver legitimately accepts undefined.

